The paper discusses deep learning approaches to structured prediction, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on multi-label classification benchmarks, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the modeling of dependencies between labels, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
